		<div id="comment_body_64211086">Nah. In the long run, basic research almost always returns massively-larger benefits than any direct problem-focused spending. That doesn't mean we shouldn't spend money on solving boring, everyday problems, we absolutely should. But we should also carve out some funding for understanding how the world works, because increasing knowledge will increase our ability to solve boring, everyday problems in ways that we cannot possibly predict.</div>
